# gen193 bilingual ratchet: the SAME conjunction/1 KB class and the SAME list
# parser, reached in Italian. "e" is a built-in conjunction; "p" is taught at
# runtime via "usa X come congiunzione" and the parser then splits on it too —
# proving the capability is in the engine+KB, not an English phrasebook.

# Built-in Italian conjunction "e" splits the list.
> torta richiede uova e farina
< Learned 2 prerequisites for torta.
# Unknown "p" is a bogus extra item until taught.
> dolce richiede zucchero p burro
< Learned 3 prerequisites for dolce.
# Teach "p" through the Italian surface; same conjunction/1 class.
> usa p come congiunzione
< Got it - I'll treat "p" as a conjunction now, like "and".
> crostata richiede noci p miele
< Learned 2 prerequisites for crostata.
> come faccio crostata
< To make crostata: noci, miele, then crostata.
